Name: Compute
Description: This contains information regarding compute instances and the data extracted and organised

Name: Detail Fact
Description: Captures measures in terms of core-hours.

Name: Host Dim
Description: All hosts (BM and Hypervisor) in Compute control plane

Name: Instance Dim
Description: All instances (BM, VM, hypervisor) are captured in this table. There are 3 types of data: 1 BM - Bare metal instances. server_key maps to host_key in compute_host_dim. Hypervisor instances are considered BM instances in this table 2 SLOT - instances launched on legacy slots. server_key maps to capacity_key in compute_vm_capacity_dim 3 BIN - instances launched on bin-packing capacity. server_key maps to attachment_key in compute_attachment_dim

Name: Pool Dim
Description: Used for capacity reporting by pool name by the Compute team

Name: Shape Family Dim
Description: This captures shape family and applies only to bin-packing capacity

Name: State Dim
Description: This has all compute states and is used to define capacity categories

Name: VM Capacity Dim
Description: This catures two types of capacity: 1 VM_CAPACITY_TYPE='SLOT' - legacy slot capacity 2 VM_CAPACITY_TYPE='BIN' - unused bin-packing capacity

Name: Cores
Description: server_type='VM' in bin-packing model: remaining cores on a capacity partition others: cores on host or slot

Name: Server Key
Description: server_type='BM': references host_key in compute_host_dim server_type='VM': references capacity_key in compute_vm_capacity_dim server_type='VMI': references attachment_key in compute_attachment_dim server_type in ('HV', 'SI'): references hypervisor_key in compute_hypervisor_dim

Name: Server Type
Description: BM: bare metal host, unused or used by BM instance VM: hypervisor capacity configured but not yet used to run VM instances, including slots in legacy compute model and capacity partitions in bin-packing model VMI: attachments in bin-packing model HV: reserved hypervisor capacity. currently 4 cores each hypervisor but this may change in the future SI: slot inefficiency. this is capacity provisioned for hypervisors but can not be used to launch VM instances

Name: Shape
Description: server_type='VM' and bin-packing data: shape_family others: shape of host, slot, of instance

Name: State
Description: state of host or slot when there is no instance attached. otherwise this is state of the instance

Name: Image Updated
Description: Timestamp when the image is modified

Name: OS
Description: Mutable field - stores the latest OS.

Name: Server Key
Description: instance_type='BM': references host_key in compute_host_dim instance_type='SLOT': references capacity_key in compute_vm_capacity_dim where vm_capacity_type='SLOT' instance_type='BIN': references attachment_key in compute_attachment_dim

Name: Pool Category10 Description
Description: Detailed description of Pool category type 10

Name: Pool Name
Description: The name of the group which the instances are pooled together to form pools

Name: Attachment State
Description: capacity_type='VMI': attachment state others: not applicable

Name: Capacity State
Description: capacity_type in ('BM', 'BMI'): state of host capacity_type in ('VM', 'VMI'): hypervisor state for hypervisor capacity object capacity_type='HV': hardcoded state for the 4-core hypervisor instance capacity_type='SI': hardcode state for slot inefficiency

Name: Capacity Type
Description: BM: unused BM host BMI: host used by BM instance VM: unused VM capacity (slot in legacy model or capacity partition in bin-packing model) VMI: capacity used by VM instance HV: capacity used to run hypervisor instance (4 cores) SI: slot inefficiency

Name: Instance State
Description: capacity_type in ('BMI', 'VMI'): instance state others: not applicable

Name: Placement State
Description: capacity_type in ('VM', 'VMI'): placement state for hypervisor capacity partition others: not applicable

Name: Pool Type
Description: server_type in ('BM', 'VM'): compute_standard or other (everything else) others: not applicable
